{
  "text": "This could be due to spontaneous activity of peripheral nociceptors, an increased sensitivity of peripheral nociceptors to inflammatory mediators, and/or a greater concentration of circulating inflammatory mediators, a phenomenon for which there is evidence in prior migraine studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, identification of lower pain thresholds at the arms of migraine subjects suggests sensitisation of third-order neurons, above the level of the trigeminal nucleus caudalis.",
  "citation_candidates": [
